<paragraph id="0C0736939F50FF914CF55F287976FBF0" blockId="21.[151,1436,152,1100]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Remarks. 
<bibRefCitation id="68294B629F50FF914D0C5F2879B5FC38" author="Ogloblin" box="[318,507,874,900]" firstAuthor="Ogloblin" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="84 - 111" refId="ref11788" refString="Ogloblin, D. A. (1930) De quelques especes de Halticinae (Col. Chrysomelidae) de la collection de V. Motschulsky. Museo Nacional de Sciences Naturales Madrid, 10, 84 - 111." type="journal article" year="1930">Ogloblin (1930)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914E955F297BC7FC38" box="[679,905,875,900]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914E955F297BC7FC38" box="[679,905,875,900]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Phaelota variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914FFE5F297D6EFC38" authority="(Motschulsky)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[972,1312,874,900]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914FFE5F297C24FC38" box="[972,1130,875,900]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. flavipennis</emphasis>
(Motschulsky)
</taxonomicName>
. Comparison of the 
<typeStatus id="D30388319F50FF914D2E5FD07939FC10" box="[284,375,914,940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914D975FD17A78FC10" box="[421,566,915,940]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914D975FD17A78FC10" box="[421,566,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914EB85FD17B64FC10" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[650,810,915,940]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914EB85FD17B64FC10" box="[650,810,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed important characters that reliably separate these two species (see the key below) and we therefore recognize 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914FA95FF97C66FC68" box="[923,1064,955,980]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914FA95FF97C66FC68" box="[923,1064,955,980]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid. In the key this species is in the same couplet with 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914DEB5FA17A33FC40" box="[473,637,995,1020]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914DEB5FA17A37FC40" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[473,633,995,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">P. flavipennis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which it can be easily differentiated by the median lobe of the aedeagus with two abruptly ending impressions basally (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F50FF914F1C58487BC8FB98" box="[814,902,1034,1060]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="22.[151,269,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[255,1339,195,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-48@22.[247,1345,183,1939]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Phaelota variabilis. 70 - dorsal habitus, 71 – pronotum, 72 – metafemur, 73 – head, 74 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views; 75 – antenna." pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F50FF914F8958497C19FB98" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[955,1111,1035,1060]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F50FF914F8958497C19FB98" box="[955,1111,1035,1060]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the impressions end gradually (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F50FF914CE158707964FBF0" box="[211,298,1074,1100]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[248,1321,203,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[245,1343,197,1953]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Phaelota flavipennis. 7 – dorsal habitus, 8 – pronotum, 9 – metafemur, 10 – head, 11 – antenna, 12 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
